<article-title>Directed Migration of Positively Selected Thymocytes Visualized in Real Time</article-title>
</related-article></article-meta></front><body><p>In <italic>PLoS Biology</italic>, volume 3, issue 6: DOI: <ext-link ext-link-type="doi" xlink:href="10.1371/journal.pbio.0030160">10.1371/journal.pbio.0030160</ext-link>
</p><p>The following statement in the last paragraph of the Results contains a factual error: &#x0201c;A total of 34% of cortical thymocytes expressing the P14 TCR had motility rates greater than 13 &#x003bc;m/min compared to approximately 2% for wild-type thymocytes expressing diverse TCRs.&#x0201d; The sentence should read as follows: &#x0201c;A total of 20% of cortical thymocytes expressing the P14 TCR had motility rates greater than 13 &#x003bc;m/min compared to approximately 2% for wild-type thymocytes expressing diverse TCRs.&#x0201d;</p><p>The authors apologize for any confusion this error may have caused.</p></body><back><fn-group><fn id="n1"><p>This correction note may be found online at DOI: <ext-link ext-link-type="doi" xlink:href="10.1371/journal.pbio.0030373">10.1371/journal.pbio.0030373</ext-link>. Published October 11, 2005</p></fn><fn id="n2" fn-type="other"><p>Citation: (2005) Correction: Directed migration of positively selected thymocytes visualized in real time. PLoS Biol 3(10): e373.</p></fn></fn-group></back></article>
